EID.description: Identification code for this event, if one exists.

log.description: Raw text message of entire event. Used to demonstrate log integrity.

user.description: Short name or login of the user.

DevicePath.description: Device that is the source of the file.

FullPath.description: Full path to the file, including the file name. It should include the drive letter, when appropriate.

Drive.description: Drive letter where the file is located. This field is only relevant on Windows.

FileName.description: Name of the file including the extension, without the directory.

Modified.description: Last time the file content was modified.

Accessed.description: Last time the file was accessed.

Changed.description: Last time the file attributes or metadata changed.

SecurityID.description: The user ID (UID) or security identifier (SID) of the file owner. (example: 1001)

SecurityType.description: Maybe file.type? (File type (file, dir, or symlink).) But the type here is SIDTypes, so maybe not...

INode.description: Inode representing the file in the filesystem. (example: 256383)

Path.description: Full path, including hive, key and value.

Type.description: Standard registry type for encoding contents. example: REG_SZ

Username.description: Short name or login of the user.

ValueName.description: Name of the value written. example: Debugger
